Swiss Franc Falls Against Euro After Strengthening Toward Parity Yesterday

-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n   a n d   S i m o n e   M e i e r
-- 
2011-08-10T05:50:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/swiss-franc-falls-against-euro-after-strengthening-toward-parity-yesterday.html
The Swiss franc depreciated against
the euro and the dollar after rising toward parity yesterday
against the 17-nation European currency.  The franc slid as much as 1.1 percent to 1.04762 per euro,
before trading at 1.04545 as of 6:46 a.m. in  London . The Swiss
currency strengthened yesterday to 1.00749.  The franc declined 1 percent to 72.82 centimes against the
dollar.  Walter Meier, a spokesman for the  Swiss National Bank  in
Zurich, declined to comment on the francâ€™s movements.  To contact the reporter on this story:
